  "prompt": "Just started to take antidepressant as part of my treatment, what should I expect now?",
  "response": "When starting antidepressants, here are some key things to expect:\n\nInitial Side Effects:\n- Possible mild nausea\n- Changes in sleep patterns\n- Potential slight weight changes\n- Possible headaches\n- Temporary increased anxiety\n\nImprovement Timeline:\n- Usually take 2-4 weeks to start seeing benefits\n- Full effects typically emerge around 6-8 weeks\n- Gradual mood improvement, not immediate\n\nImportant Recommendations:\n- Take medication consistently at same time daily\n- Don't stop medication abruptly\n- Communicate with your doctor about any side effects\n- Continue therapy/counseling alongside medication\n- Be patient with the process\n- Avoid alcohol while on medication\n\nWarning Signs to Report to Doctor:\n- Severe side effects\n- Suicidal thoughts\n- Significant mood changes\n- Allergic reactions\n\nAdditional Advice:\n- Maintain healthy lifestyle (sleep, diet, exercise)\n- Track your mood and symptoms\n- Be open with support system about your treatment\n\nRemember, everyone's experience is unique, and finding the right medication and dosage can take time. Work closely with your healthcare provider throughout the process.",
